cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.DL, cs.CY, cs.LG 

The paper deals with information retrieval and natural language processing techniques to improve search results for a large document collection. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IR (Information Retrieval). The paper also mentions using concept extraction from Wikipedia, which falls under the category of natural language processing (cs.CL). Additionally, the use of co-occurrence statistics and machine learning techniques for query expansion and term suggestion could fall under categories such as cs.DL (Digital Libraries), cs.CY (Computers and Society), and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
